<sect5><title>Known Bugs</title>

	<orderedlist>
		<listitem>
			<para>Function arguments can be passed to array-requiring paths without complaint (e.g. old p.com, now a function)</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Rebonding model also folds atoms, making --nofold irrelevant</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Atom list update is super-slow when changing selection in big systems - This is an issue with Qt, and doesn't appear to have a resolution at present.</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Progress indicators following Disorder wizard usage appear to be prevented from appearing</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>When using default display lists for rendering, stick lists are cleared but still appear (e.g. when creating a new model)</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Disorder builder does not create an undo state.</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Changing between models leaves text labels from previous model visible until view is moved.</para>
		</listitem>
	</orderedlist>

</sect5>

